     {
      "text": "lashon pa’ul",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ") is a special type of word in Hebrew and Aramaic. ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "topLevelNodes": [
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "In English, an example of a “finished” participle is the word “written,” or the word “burnt.”",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "A finished participle represents the result of an action (eg “burnt”) as opposed to an ongoing action (eg “burning.”)",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "Students interested in grammar can read ",
